 <tr><TD bgcolor='#003366' width='655'><B><FONT face='Verdana' color=#ffffff size=3>&nbsp;&nbsp;I plead the 5th...</font></b>&nbsp;&nbsp;<font face='Verdana' size='-7' color='#FFFF00'>Rombus ~  Sunday February 3rd, 2002</font></td></tr>
	<tr><TD width=655 align='left'><font face='Verdana'><br><p align=center><font face=Verdana size=2>
<img border=0 src=images/news/02February02/vulak.jpg width=568 height=181></font></p>
<table border=0 cellpadding=2 style=border-collapse: collapse bordercolor=#111111 width=100% id=AutoNumber2>
  <tr>
    <td width=1%><font face=Verdana size=2>
    <img border=0 src=images/news/02February02/3dragon.jpg width=265 height=256></font></td>
    <td width=99%><font face=Verdana size=2>Cleared North again, nothing 
    new really... in fact, clearing North has become so routine I don't think 
    it's possible to say anything funny about it anymore. :(  </font>
    <p><font face=Verdana size=2>So yeah, we actually got some real caster 
    specific loot from Vulak this time!  Grats to Brownivy on Solist's 
    Earring (he really was a great, great man), Dainja on the Gharn's Rock of 
    'Hi I'm Taking Up a Spot in the Vulak Drop Table', and Saolor on the Earring 
    of Humbled By Luclin Drops.</font></p>
    <p><font face=Verdana size=2>What other nice shit did we pick up this 
    run?  Hrm, let's see!  We managed to grab Royce a Sprinkler of 
    Spirits, Zorulis picked up our first  Dragon Skin Wristband thing, an 
    Orb of the Deep Seas for Arma... apparently that's really all that was worth 
    mentioning.  </font></p>
    <p><font face=Verdana size=2>PS: Thank god for Paladin's... they are so 
    l337~<br>
    <img border=0 src=images/news/02February02/critloh.gif width=263 height=17></font></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<p> </p>
<table border=0 cellpadding=2 style=border-collapse: collapse bordercolor=#111111 width=100% id=AutoNumber4>
  <tr>
    <td width=100%><font face=Verdana size=2>What else did we do?  
    Well, we stopped by Kael for some more domination... alas, the Avatar of War 
    slipped through our fingers again, but rest assured the red and yellow 
    thread shall be eliminated soon.</font><p><font face=Verdana size=2>What 
    do you do when you want to kill time?  Well, we dropped Mr. Vindicator 
    (grats Megrok on the BP) and then hit up his lover Mr. Stachu (grats Garland 
    on the BP, Mardigann on the Iron Scroll, and he dropped something else but I 
    can't remember what it was... whoops!).  During both fights we noticed 
    our Monks running around, scheming and planning... for what we didn't know, 
    but we would soon find out.</font></p>
    <p><font face=Verdana size=2>What happens when you put 4 Triton Monks in 
    the Kael Arena and they get bored? 
    <a target=_blank href=images/news/02February02/tormaxpull.jpg>Tormax 
    Incoming</a>!  Yeah, that was fun. ;)  Kind of funny to see the 
    faction leaches running around the arena in shock because they weren't 
    expecting to see the ruler of Kael up there.</font></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<p> </p>
<table border=0 cellpadding=2 style=border-collapse: collapse bordercolor=#111111 width=100% id=AutoNumber3>
  <tr>
    <td width=91%><font face=Verdana size=2>In search of something to do, 
    for the first time in forever we hopped over to Akheva to work on our 
    whisperling faction.  Err no wait, that's what the point of the raid 
    ended up being AFTER we killed the mob we were there for because his loot 
    was so TOTALLY USELESS!</font><p><font face=Verdana size=2>Yeah, dropped 
    The Itraer Vius v2.0, less phat lewts for twice the challenge... yey risk 
    vs. reward.  What kind of joke is this?  Heck, I could go over to 
    Ssra and kill the first Rhag with a group of 6 and get better crap than 
    this.  Oh well, Grats Maace on the Sword and Kotori 'Sunshine' on the 
    Sunbeam Staff.</font></p>
    <p><font face=Verdana size=2>In my opinion, the best part about Luclin 
    fights is the
    <a target=_blank href=images/news/02February02/lookatthefeet.jpg>diverse 
    environments</a> you encounter... *grin*</font></p>
    <p><font face=Verdana size=2>We also payed a visit to the Thought Horror 
    Overfiend who dropped an Orb of the Lost Souls for Iadar and some spells.  
    They really need to make this guy harder... oh well, at least getting to him 
    is fun!<br>
 </font></p>
